OL,3,C'No significant operational impact'
OL,4,Cfrom absence of Police Ombudsman: Long
OL,6,FMs Long was questioned by MLAs around
OL,7,Fthe situation following an urgent oral
OL,8,Fquestion at the Assembly submitted by
OL,9,FUUP leader Doug Beattie.
OL,11,FMr Beattie asked for an update on the
OL,12,Foperational capacity of the Police
OL,13,FOmbudsman's Office, describing a
OL,14,F"critical role".
OL,16,FMs Long responded: "There will be no
OL,17,Fsignificant operational impact on the
OL,18,Foffice's capacity due to the Police
OL,19,FOmbudsman's absence. The ombudsman has
OL,20,Fdelegated her powers to the senior
OL,21,Fdirector of investigations."
