OL,3,C'No significant operational impact'
OL,4,Cfrom absence of Police Ombudsman: Long
OL,6,FMeanwhile, TUV MLA Jim Allister
OL,7,Fquestioned whether it is "untenable
OL,8,Ffor this office to continue rudderless
OL,9,Fwith no ombudsman and no chief
OL,10,Fexecutive", adding: "Doesn't the
OL,11,Fombudsman need to step aside?"
OL,13,FMs Long responded by saying that is a
OL,14,Fmatter for the ombudsman in the first
OL,15,Finstance, and for the First and deputy
OL,16,FFirst Minister who appoint the role in
OL,17,Fthe second instance.
